items.name: Vitamin D
items.description: Its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant and neuroprotective properties support immune health, muscle function and brain cell activity. It can be found on fortified milk, fortified cereal, and fatty fish such as salmon, mackerel and sardines.

items.name: Vitamin E
items.description: Vitamin E is a nutrient that's important to vision, reproduction, and the health of your blood, brain and skin.Foods rich in vitamin E include canola oil, olive oil, margarine, almonds and peanuts. You can also get vitamin E from meats, dairy, leafy greens and fortified cereals.
